    "In conclusion, most conventional methods used to solve rule-based puzzles employ deterministic approaches that reliably produce solutions, in stark contrast to the unpredictable nature of LLMs.",
    "Another advantage of these traditional methods is their explainability and interpretability, crucial attributes for thoroughly evaluating algorithms and understanding their decision-making processes.",
    "However, as demonstrated in the study by Takano (2023), these methods can sometimes exhibit increased time complexity, indicating a potential trade-off between reliability and efficiency.",
    "Table 1 delineates the various methods leveraged for puzzle-solving based on the datasets we have collected, illustrating the landscape of current LLM research in this domain.",
    "It particularly highlights the extensive methods applied to rule-based deterministic and rule-less commonsense puzzles."
